I’m currently a PhD student in Computer Science at Northeastern University (2024 – present), working with Dr. David Bau on mechanistic interpretability for code LLMs—data attribution, representation learning, and causality.

I earned a Master of Science in Engineering in Biomedical Engineering from Johns Hopkins University (2020 – 2022), focusing on machine learning and data science under the mentorship of Dr. Joshua Vogelstein. My thesis, “Hands‑On Network Machine Learning,” later became the basis for a Cambridge University Press textbook. I graduated with highest honors, made the dean’s list, and held a 3.97 / 4.0 GPA.

My undergraduate degree is a B.S. in Behavioral Neuroscience from Western Washington University (2014 – 2018), with minors in Chemistry and Philosophy. While there I founded and presided over the Computational Neuroscience Club, building it from scratch and teaching weekly seminars.
